Date: «[Date of Issue]»

To: [Candidate Full Name]  
Address: [Candidate Address]

Subject: Offer of Internship (AI Intern) — Fixed Term

Dear [Candidate Full Name],

We are pleased to offer you a fixed-term internship with Omninuera in the position of **AI Intern** on the terms set out in this letter. This offer is subject to the terms and conditions described below and to your acceptance of this letter.

1. Position and Reporting
- Role Title: AI Intern.  
- Reporting Line: [Reporting Manager / Team].  
- Employment Type: Fixed-term internship for a period of **3 (three) months** starting on **[Start Date]** (the "Start Date"). The internship will end automatically on the date that is three months from the Start Date unless extended in writing by mutual agreement.

2. Work Location and Jurisdiction
- Work Location: Fully remote, with the intern based in Bengaluru, India. All governance, applicable employment considerations, and jurisdictional references in this letter are aligned to Bengaluru, India. HR to ensure compliance with applicable local requirements.

3. Compensation
- Stipend: INR 10,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Thousand) per month, subject to applicable statutory deductions.  
- Payment Schedule: [Payment schedule details — e.g., monthly in arrears by the last working day of each month; enter bank details for disbursement].  
- The stipend is intended as a training/learning stipend and not a salary or wage for employment purposes.

4. Duration and Extension
- Term: This internship is for a fixed term of 3 months commencing on [Start Date] and ending on [End Date = Start Date + 3 months], unless earlier terminated under the termination provisions below. Any extension must be agreed in writing by both parties.

5. Working Hours and Attendance
- Working Hours: [Working Hours / Weekly Time Commitment]. Expected to be available during mutually agreed core hours and to attend scheduled meetings, reviews, and team activities.  
- Absence: Planned leave should be communicated and approved in advance. Unplanned absence should be notified to the reporting manager as soon as reasonably practicable.

6. Benefits
- The intern will receive no benefits other than the stipend unless HR specifies standard intern perks.  
- Optional standard intern perks (if any): [Standard Intern Perks (optional) — e.g., access to learning resources, mentorship, networking events, remote equipment reimbursement]. HR to complete if applicable.

7. Confidentiality
- During and after the internship, you shall keep confidential all non-public information, trade secrets, business plans, algorithms, models, datasets, customer information, and other confidential or proprietary information of Omninuera and its clients (together, "Confidential Information"), and shall not disclose such information except as authorised by Omninuera in writing.

8. Intellectual Property and Work Product
- You agree that all inventions, discoveries, improvements, developments, works of authorship, models, data, software, documentation, designs, processes, or other materials conceived, created, authored, contributed to, or reduced to practice by you, alone or jointly with others, during the internship and relating to Omninuera's business or using Omninuera resources (collectively, "Work Product"), are the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera.  
- You hereby assign (or agree to assign) to Omninuera all right, title, and interest in such Work Product and will execute any documents reasonably required to effectuate such assignment.

9. Termination
- Termination for Convenience: Either party may terminate this internship for convenience by providing [Notice Period for Termination / For Convenience] prior written notice (or payment/stipend in lieu, if applicable). HR to specify notice period.  
- Termination for Cause: Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including but not limited to material breach of this letter, misconduct, violation of policies, gross negligence, willful damage to company systems, or criminal activity.  
- Effect of Termination: Upon termination, you must return all company property and Confidential Information. Any stipend owed up to the date of termination will be paid pro rata as per company policy.

10. Compliance with Company Policies and Code of Conduct
- You are required to comply with Omninuera's policies, including but not limited to policies on acceptable use, information security, data protection, anti-harassment, and the company code of conduct. HR will provide relevant policy documents which form part of this engagement.

11. Background Checks
- This offer is conditional upon satisfactory completion of any background checks required by Omninuera. Details of the scope and vendor (if any) to be provided by HR: [Background Check Scope / Vendor Details].

12. Data Protection and Privacy
- Omninuera will process your personal information in accordance with applicable data protection laws and Omninuera's privacy policies. By accepting this offer, you consent to such processing for purposes related to your internship and related administrative matters.

13. Taxes and Statutory Deductions
- You will be responsible for any personal taxes resulting from the stipend. Omninuera may make statutory deductions from the stipend where required by law and will comply with statutory reporting obligations.

14. No Guarantee of Future Employment
- This internship does not constitute a promise of employment. Any offer of further employment after the internship must be in writing and signed by an authorised representative of Omninuera.

15. Miscellaneous
- Entire Agreement: This letter sets out the terms of the internship and supersedes any prior discussions or understandings on this subject.  
- Amendments: Any amendment to this letter must be in writing and signed by both parties.  
- Severability: If any provision of this letter is found unenforceable, the remainder shall remain in full force and effect.  
- Assignment: Omninuera may assign this letter or any of its rights hereunder.

16. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
- This letter and any dispute or claim arising out of or in connection with it shall be governed by the laws applicable in Bengaluru, India. The courts located in Bengaluru, India shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any such dispute.

17. Acceptance
To indicate your acceptance of this offer, please sign and return a scanned copy of this letter to HR at [HR Contact Email] by [Acceptance Deadline, if any].

Accepted and agreed:

